o1.15"},"abstract":[{"text":"The library has been completely updated for Swift 6 language mode, and now compiles in strict","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"concurrency with no warnings or errors.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.15"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The library is now 100% Swift 6 compatible, and has been done in a way that is full backwards","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"compatible. If your project does not have strict concurrency warnings turned on, then updating","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the Composable Architecture to 1.15.0 should not cause any compilation errors. However, if you have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"strict concurrency turned on, then you may come across a few situations you need to update.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Enum-cases-as-function-references","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Enum cases as function references"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is common to use the case of enum as a function, such as mapping on an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Effect","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to bundle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"its output into an action:"}]},{"code":["return client.fetch()","  .map(Action.response)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In strict concurrency mode this may fail with a message like this:","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"🛑 Converting non-sendable function value to ‘@Sendable (Value) -> Action’ may introduce data races"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There are two ways to fix this. You can either open the closure explicitly instead of using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"Action.response","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as a function:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["return client.fetch()","  .map { .response($0) }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There is also an upcoming Swift feature that will fix this. You can enable it in an SPM package","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by adding a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enableUpcomingFeature"},{"text":" to its Swift settings:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["swiftSettings: [","  .enableUpcomingFeature(\"InferSendableFromCaptures\"),","]),"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And you can ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/blog\/using-upcoming-feature-flags\/","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by navigating to your project’s build settings in Xcode, and adding a new “Other Swift Flags” flag:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["-enable-upcoming-feature InferSendableFromCaptures"],"syntax":null}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/Reducer/dependency(_:)":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Places a value in the reducer’s dependencies."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/dependency(_:)","title":"dependency(_:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"dependency"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"Value"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Value"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"_DependencyKeyWritingReducer"},{"kin